How to Ask for This Haircut at the Salon:
	1.	Top Length:
	•	Ask for around 4–5 inches on top with layers for volume and movement.
	•	Mention you want a textured look, not flat or overly sleek.
	2.	Sides & Back:
	•	Request a tapered scissor cut instead of a machine fade. This keeps it natural and balanced.
	•	Tell the barber to blend the sides into the top smoothly (no hard disconnect).
	3.	Fringe / Front Section:
	•	Leave the front slightly longer, enough to fall over the forehead if styled that way.
	•	Add light texture to avoid a blocky or heavy look.
	4.	Styling:
	•	Use a light matte wax or cream for hold with natural texture.
	•	Blow-dry from the back to front, using your fingers or a round brush to lift the roots for volume.

⸻

Ideal for:
	•	Medium to thick hair types.
	•	Oval, heart, or square face shapes.
